Performs a mathematical operation on two numbers or strings

Inputs\:
value1 - The first value.
value2 - The second value.
operation - The operation to perform (+ - * ^ / > < \=\= \!\= >\= <\=).

failure - Something went wrong or the boolean operation returned false.

6b29c02c-9818-46f1-8a02-6b468d452539.69c7db92-7c96-4c2d-9b44-e099cad3d4ec.description=
Compares two strings, returning a true response if and only if they contain the same sequence of characters. A null string is considered to be equal to an empty string.

Inputs\:
string1 - The first string.
string2 - The second string.
ignoreCase - If set to 'true', then the comparison ignores case considerations. The two strings are considered equal ignoring case if they are of the same length and corresponding characters in the two strings are equal ignoring case. If set to any value other than 'true', then the strings must match exactly to be considered equal.

responses\:
true - If the two strings are equal
false - If the two strings are not equal

6b29c02c-9818-46f1-8a02-6b468d452539.description=
Synopsis

    This flow creates a NAS failover group.
    createSusNasFailoverGroup performs the following steps\:
      1. Retrieve a list of elligible vLans with the HPOO flow getVlans.
      2. Iterate through the list of vLans based on the variable input numVlanRecords.
      3. Determine whether there are existing vLans based on the vLan ID.
      4. Using XSLT, retrieve a list of vLans that fit the input criteria.
      5. Determine if there is an existing vLan on the node and port.
      6. Determine whether to extend the existing vLan or create a new one.
      7. Create a new vLan (if not extending an existing one) with the HPOO flow createVlan.
      8. Retrieve a list of failover groups to assign with the HPOO flow getFailoverGroups.
      9. If no elligible failover groups exist, create a new failover group.

Inputs

    clusterName - The IP or host name of the NetApp cluster (required).
      Valid values\: Dot-decimal notation IPv4 address or RFC 1123 compliant host name.
      Default value\: None.

    node - The contoller node for the clusterName (required).
    physical port - The actual port that the LIF is assigned to  (required). 
    vLanId - The name of the vLan used in the flow (required).
    failoverGroup - The failover group assigned to the cluster (required).
    extendVlan -  (required).
      Valid values\: Implementation-specific.
      Default value\: None.

    overrideJRAS - Value to override the system-defined Java RAS server.
      Valid values\: Implementation specific.
      Default value\: Hosting Eng RAS.

    numVlanRecords - (required).
      Valid values\: 
      Default value\:

Results

    hpooFlowResult - The XML response specific to the functionality of the flow;  {what does this flow return and how is it returned?}  See Notes section for more details.
    flowStatus - Overall status of the flow, value is one of the string literals "success" or "failed".

Responses

    Success - All operations and subflows completed successfully.
    Failure - Some operations and/or subflows failed.
    fgExists - The failover group already exists.

Notes

    1. Anything else the caller or support person may need to know about the flow. Relationships that aren't easily inferred, abmnormal flow behaviors, hard-codings, etc.
